data.chText: 使昏迷；（尤指）打昏
data.enText: to make a person or an animal unconscious for a short time, especially by hitting them on the head

data.chText: 那一下摔得我昏迷了片刻。
data.enText: The fall stunned me for a moment.

data.chText: 屠宰前要先把动物击昏。
data.enText: The animals are stunned before slaughter.

data.chText: 使震惊（或惊愕、目瞪口呆）
data.enText: to surprise or shock sb so much that they cannot think clearly or speak

data.chText: 给（某人）以深刻印象；使深深感动
data.enText: to impress sb very much

data.chText: 在峰顶看到的景色使他们惊叹不已。
data.enText: They were stunned by the view from the summit.

data.chText: 她惊愕得说不出话来。
data.enText: She was too stunned to speak.

data.chText: 我把消息讲了后，他们惊愕得哑然一片。
data.enText: There was a stunned silence when I told them the news.

data.text: surprise ♦ startle ♦ amaze ♦ stun ♦ astonish ♦ take sb aback ♦ astound

data.chText: 以上各词均含使惊奇、使诧异之义。
data.enText: These words all mean to make sb feel surprised.
surprise

data.chText: 指使惊奇、使诧异、使感到意外：
data.enText: to give sb the feeling that you get when sth happens that you do not expect or do not understand, or sth that you do expect does not happen; to make sb feel surprised

data.chText: 这一结果完全在我的意料之中。
data.enText: The outcome didn't surprise me at all.
startle

data.chText: 指惊吓、使吓一跳、使大吃一惊：
data.enText: to surprise sb suddenly in a way that slightly shocks or frightens them

data.chText: 对不起，我不是存心要吓唬你。
data.enText: Sorry, I didn't mean to startle you.

data.chText: 爆炸声使马受了惊。
data.enText: The explosion startled the horse.
amaze

data.chText: 指使惊奇、使惊愕、使惊诧：
data.enText: to surprise sb very much

data.chText: 仅仅地方之大就使她十分惊奇。
data.enText: Just the huge size of the place amazed her.
stun

data.chText: （常用于报章）指使震惊、使惊愕、使目瞪口呆
data.enText: ( rather informal ) (often in newspapers) to surprise or shock sb so much that they cannot think clearly or speak
astonish

data.chText: 指使十分惊讶、使大为惊奇：
data.enText: to surprise sb very much

data.chText: 这消息使大家十分惊讶。
data.enText: The news astonished everyone.

data.chText: 用amaze还是astonish？
上述两词意思相同，多数情况下使用任何一个均可。astonish总的说来比amaze的使用频率稍低。但如果指某事既使人惊愕又使人羞愧则较常用astonish：
data.enText: These two words have the same meaning and in most cases you can use either. Astonish is in general slightly less frequent than amaze , but if you are talking about sth that both surprises you and makes you feel ashamed, it is more usual to use astonish .

data.chText: 他对自己的愚蠢感到十分震惊。
data.enText: He was astonished by his own stupidity.
amaze or astonish?
take sb aback

data.chText: （尤指不好的事）使大吃一惊、使震惊：
data.enText: [usually passive] (especially of sth negative) to surprise or shock sb

data.chText: 她敌视的反应使我们大吃一惊。
data.enText: We were rather taken aback by her hostile reaction.
astound

data.chText: 指使震惊、使大惊：
data.enText: to surprise or shock sb very much

data.chText: 他的傲慢使她震惊。
data.enText: His arrogance astounded her.
It surprises sb/startles sb/amazes sb/stuns sb/astonishes sb/takes sb aback/astounds sb
to surprise/startle/amaze/stun/astonish/astound sb that…
to surprise/amaze sb what/how…
to surprise/startle/amaze/stun/astonish/astound sb to know/find/learn/see/hear…
to be surprised/startled/stunned into (doing) sth
to absolutely amaze sb/stun sb/astonish sb/astound sb
sth never ceases to surprise/amaze/astonish/astound sb

means: 使震惊(或惊愕、目瞪口呆)

tr: make senseless or dizzy by or as if by a blow
hit something or somebody as if with a sandbag
overcome as with astonishment or disbelief

value.def: If you are stunned by something, you are extremely shocked or surprised by it and are therefore unable to speak or do anything.

example.ex: Many cinema-goers were stunned by the film's violent and tragic end.
example.tran: 许多来看电影的人都被这部影片暴力而悲惨的结局所震惊。

value.tran: 使震惊;使目瞪口呆;使惊愕

example.ex: When they told me she had gone missing I was totally stunned...
example.tran: 他们告诉我她不见了时，我当时完全惊呆了。

example.ex: His announcement did not produce any immediate cheers, only a stunned silence while the words sank in.
example.tran: 他的声明并没有当即引起什么欢呼，人们在领会了他的话后，只有一片令人意想不到的沉默。

value.def: If something such as a blow on the head stuns you, it makes you unconscious or confused and unsteady.

example.ex: Sam stood his ground and got a blow that stunned him.
example.tran: 萨姆站在原地，被一下打昏了。

trans: 眩晕弹，震撼手榴弹(使人无法动弹但不会造成重创)
眩晕枪(一种使人或动物短时失去知觉或无法动弹的武器)
